abstract: Some drivers in Queens and Brooklyn worry their commuting costs could go up with a new congestion plan. They oppose tolls on the East River bridges.
snippet: Some drivers in Queens and Brooklyn worry their commuting costs could go up with a new congestion plan. They oppose tolls on the East River bridges.
lead_paragraph: The closest subway station to Bob Friedrich’s home in eastern Queens is 10 miles away, so he drives to work in Manhattan at least three times a week.

abstract: With Mayor de Blasio having alienated some luminaries who attended his first inauguration, his second swearing-in will have a pared-down look.
snippet: With Mayor de Blasio having alienated some luminaries who attended his first inauguration, his second swearing-in will have a pared-down look.
lead_paragraph: When Bill de Blasio was sworn in for his first term as mayor, before a crowd of thousands on Jan. 1, 2014, the event seemed like a political coronation, celebrating New York City’s return to Democratic rule.

lead_paragraph: How do New York Times journalists use technology in their jobs and in their personal lives? Michael de la Merced, a DealBook reporter for The Times based in London, discussed the tech he is using.

abstract: A New York task force weighs a new fee on rides in for-hire vehicles in Manhattan, which would be paid by riders and raise money to fix the subways.
snippet: A New York task force weighs a new fee on rides in for-hire vehicles in Manhattan, which would be paid by riders and raise money to fix the subways.
lead_paragraph: The sputtering traffic in Manhattan has long been blamed on cars and delivery trucks pouring onto the streets from the rest of the city and beyond.

abstract: Just days after the price of Bitcoin nearly reached $20,000, the virtual currency was hit by a panicked sell-off. Reddit users posted suicide hotlines.
snippet: Just days after the price of Bitcoin nearly reached $20,000, the virtual currency was hit by a panicked sell-off. Reddit users posted suicide hotlines.
lead_paragraph: You can’t exactly say that Bitcoin was burning a hole in anyone’s pocket, but the virtual currency burned a hole in quite a few hearts on Friday when it plunged 30 percent in less than 24 hours after defying gravity for the past few months.

abstract: With Carmen Fariña stepping down, the de Blasio administration is searching for a successor, but what the mayor wants to accomplish is unclear.
snippet: With Carmen Fariña stepping down, the de Blasio administration is searching for a successor, but what the mayor wants to accomplish is unclear.
lead_paragraph: Seated next to Mayor Bill de Blasio in the Blue Room at City Hall on Thursday, the retiring schools chancellor, Carmen Fariña, 74, offered her own summation of her tenure as the leader of what is in effect a medium-size city, populated by 1.1 million students and 75,000 teachers, and with a $30 billion annual budget.
